WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.003
JOE:
Previously on Hardy Boys....

00:03.003 --> 00:04.505
- Clear the area! There's a bomb!

00:04.505 --> 00:06.507
[explosion]
[screaming]

00:06.507 --> 00:08.342
Did the bomb take out the phone lines?

00:08.342 --> 00:10.093
- Yeah, the alarm company techs

00:10.093 --> 00:12.262
are trying to get their system
up and running, too.

00:12.262 --> 00:13.680
JOE:
Wilt's was never the target.

00:13.680 --> 00:15.349
It's just a decoy.

00:15.349 --> 00:16.558
♪

00:16.558 --> 00:17.893
This must have been the point of entry.

00:18.852 --> 00:20.521
- There's a crystal missing.

00:20.521 --> 00:22.606
PHIL:
Flash Stones. They're a local legend.

00:22.606 --> 00:25.400
Some New Age weirdos think
they contain high vibrational energy.

00:25.400 --> 00:27.611
FRANK: George pulled it out
of the ground at the beach. I saw him.

00:27.611 --> 00:29.655
CALLIE: When did you see this?
- I saw it in a vision.

00:30.614 --> 00:33.367
- Frank never had The Eye.
He is The Eye.

00:33.992 --> 00:34.993
[grunts]

00:34.993 --> 00:37.621
[tumbling]
But we're not telling anyone.

00:37.621 --> 00:39.331
BELINDA:
Clearly, she's into something shady,

00:39.331 --> 00:40.958
and my dad could be in danger.

00:40.958 --> 00:43.544
CHET: Instead of going right at your dad,
we ease up

00:43.544 --> 00:44.878
in case he's shady, too.

00:46.046 --> 00:47.339
- You told me to keep you in check.

00:47.339 --> 00:48.507
- Just trust me!

00:48.507 --> 00:49.967
The Eye will lead us to the crystal.

00:49.967 --> 00:52.469
The crystal will lead us to that
shadow man from my vision!

00:52.469 --> 00:54.596
- We didn't need The Eye last year.

00:54.596 --> 00:56.640
Maybe we don't need it at all now.

01:02.062 --> 01:05.065
[high-pitched tone]

01:10.153 --> 01:13.156
[tone continues]

01:13.907 --> 01:14.950
[grunts]

01:17.035 --> 01:18.078
[gasps]

01:20.914 --> 01:22.708
[coughing]

01:22.708 --> 01:24.251
[Frank groans]

01:25.460 --> 01:26.461
[tone stops]

01:26.461 --> 01:29.089
[panting]

01:29.089 --> 01:32.009
- There. That's much better.

01:32.009 --> 01:34.803
[heavy breathing]

01:34.803 --> 01:36.221
- You found the Flash Stone.

01:36.221 --> 01:38.765
- I really must quit leaving
my journal lying around.

01:38.765 --> 01:40.225
- You didn't write much about it.

01:40.225 --> 01:42.394
- Not in my journal, no.

01:42.394 --> 01:44.313
Mustn't keep all my secrets in one place.

01:45.189 --> 01:47.024
- What is that?
- Why...

01:48.317 --> 01:50.861
it's everything. I'll show you.

01:54.573 --> 01:56.200
Find a good spot.

01:58.202 --> 01:59.703
A little to the right.

02:00.454 --> 02:02.331
Good. To the right.

02:03.874 --> 02:05.083
Forward.

02:06.460 --> 02:07.961
Now to the left.

02:07.961 --> 02:09.505
[scoffs]

02:09.505 --> 02:10.923
Back to the right.

02:12.966 --> 02:15.135
Now, slide down the screen
on the wall for me.

02:15.135 --> 02:18.138
♪

02:21.099 --> 02:22.976
[rattling]

02:22.976 --> 02:24.978
Now, push it until it clicks.

02:25.395 --> 02:26.396
[click]

02:27.147 --> 02:28.649
Now, turn.

02:29.858 --> 02:31.151
What do you see?

02:31.151 --> 02:33.654
[projector whirring]

02:41.620 --> 02:43.580
- I see the past.
I see you at the beach.

02:43.580 --> 02:45.082
- That's not me.

02:45.082 --> 02:47.417
That's George Estabrook.

02:47.417 --> 02:49.086
I'm just in your head.

02:49.086 --> 02:51.296
A projection of The Eye.

02:51.296 --> 02:53.298
[projector whirring]

03:03.267 --> 03:04.810
♪

03:04.810 --> 03:06.687
- Did you just have a vision?

03:06.687 --> 03:09.147
- Yeah.
[shuts off engine]

03:09.147 --> 03:12.025
- Sorry, sometimes I don't even realize
they're happening right away.

03:12.025 --> 03:14.820
- Okay. What did you see just now?

03:14.820 --> 03:17.239
- George transformed
the Flash Stone from the beach.

03:17.781 --> 03:19.908
It was making an awful noise,

03:19.908 --> 03:22.035
like something was deep inside of it.

03:22.035 --> 03:23.871
- Like... like what?

03:23.871 --> 03:26.874
- I don't know.
Like-like a power or-or an energy.

03:27.499 --> 03:29.918
George said it's everything.

03:30.836 --> 03:31.837
- Spooky.

03:32.754 --> 03:34.631
Okay, we'll figure it out.

03:34.631 --> 03:37.217
[quiet chatter outside]
[birds chirping]

03:37.217 --> 03:39.178
You sure you're ready for this?

03:39.178 --> 03:41.972
- Yeah. Yeah, I have to be.

03:41.972 --> 03:44.850
I mean, the crystal started with George,
but it ended up with Gloria.

03:46.059 --> 03:47.436
Let's do this.

03:47.436 --> 03:50.439
♪

03:52.816 --> 03:54.359
[car doors shut]

03:57.738 --> 04:00.741
[radio static, distortions]
[door opens]

04:01.950 --> 04:04.328
[banging]

04:06.163 --> 04:07.831
- Whatcha doing?
- What are you doing?

04:07.831 --> 04:10.292
The doors closed for a reason!
I could've been changing!

04:10.292 --> 04:11.293
BIFF:
Well, you're not.

04:11.293 --> 04:13.670
You're beating up a CB radio
for some reason.

04:13.670 --> 04:16.423
- I'm trying to contact JB.
- Why?

04:16.423 --> 04:17.798
[shuts door]

04:17.798 --> 04:19.635
- [sighs] We need to get
The Eye out of Frank.

04:19.635 --> 04:21.512
- I thought it was helping.

04:21.512 --> 04:22.888
- It's not.

04:22.888 --> 04:24.640
Something's changed in him, okay?
I can tell.

04:24.640 --> 04:27.768
He went from not wanting anybody
to know to telling everybody.

04:27.768 --> 04:29.686
And he didn't even talk it over with me.

04:29.686 --> 04:31.230
- Sounds like it's more
about you than him.

04:31.230 --> 04:33.774
- He told me to keep him in check, okay?
So, that's what I'm doing.

04:33.774 --> 04:36.485
Except JB's not answering.
I mean, why make a way to reach out

04:36.485 --> 04:37.861
if you're not gonna bother reaching back?

04:37.861 --> 04:39.863
- Yeah, hard to believe
you can't count on a career criminal.

04:39.863 --> 04:42.115
- He's our best shot at stealing the relic
from the Stratemeyer vault.

04:42.115 --> 04:43.784
- Which is where?

04:44.493 --> 04:45.994
- I'm working on that.

04:47.287 --> 04:50.290
Once we get the relic,
we can get the power out of Frank.

04:52.417 --> 04:54.336
I'm working on that, too!

04:54.336 --> 04:56.797
But if the power can transfer
out of the relic into Frank,

04:56.797 --> 04:58.423
it should be possible
to reverse the process.

04:58.423 --> 05:01.134
[radio static, chatter]
- What does Frank think of all this?

05:04.096 --> 05:06.265
Oh. I see. We're not telling Frank.

05:07.224 --> 05:09.059
This will end well.

05:09.059 --> 05:10.310
[opens door]

05:11.728 --> 05:12.980
[shuts door]
[sighs]

05:18.151 --> 05:19.361
- Mm...

05:20.445 --> 05:22.197
Francis.

05:22.197 --> 05:23.615
Oh...

05:23.615 --> 05:25.617
I'm so happy to see you.

05:26.410 --> 05:29.788
[sighs] I wish that you would come
every single day.

05:31.039 --> 05:33.834
Well, let me show you around the grounds.

05:33.834 --> 05:37.504
I mean, for a prison, they're quite nice.
We have some rather lovely flowers.

05:37.504 --> 05:39.965
- And to think, some prisons
don't even have flowers.

05:39.965 --> 05:41.925
- [laughs] Callie.

05:41.925 --> 05:45.387
Oh, in case you were
reconsidering my offer,

05:45.387 --> 05:48.765
just one phone call to
Rosegrave would do the trick.

05:49.933 --> 05:51.935
- We came here about something else.
- Hm.

05:53.187 --> 05:54.771
- You heard about the bombing at Wilt's.

05:54.771 --> 05:56.315
- Oh, of course.

05:56.315 --> 05:58.984
Well, I get updates from town every day.

05:58.984 --> 06:00.819
That was quite unfortunate.

06:01.486 --> 06:03.197
See what happens
when I'm not around?

06:03.197 --> 06:05.365
- Yeah. Well, it turns out the bombing

06:05.365 --> 06:06.950
was a cover-up for another crime.

06:08.702 --> 06:10.120
There was a robbery.

06:10.787 --> 06:11.997
At your house.

06:11.997 --> 06:15.042
- That's not possible.
I have round-the-clock security.

06:15.042 --> 06:17.336
- Yes, but Elekton Security Controls

06:17.336 --> 06:19.046
didn't know the robbery ever happened.

06:19.046 --> 06:21.632
The bombing took out
their main communications relay.

06:21.632 --> 06:24.051
Anyone in town using that alarm company

06:24.051 --> 06:27.346
wouldn't have a working system
for 60 seconds, including you.

06:27.346 --> 06:30.432
- What did they take?
I mean, art? My jewelry?

06:30.432 --> 06:31.725
CALLIE:
Nothing obvious.

06:31.725 --> 06:35.229
In fact, we don't really understand
why anyone would want this item at all.

06:35.771 --> 06:37.272
- "This item"?

06:38.607 --> 06:39.608
♪

06:39.608 --> 06:40.442
You know what they took.

06:42.069 --> 06:45.739
You know, and you are
going to tell me right now!

06:45.739 --> 06:48.534
- It was a crystal from your chandelier.

06:48.534 --> 06:51.078
- No. No, no, no.

06:51.078 --> 06:52.704
- The Flash Stone, what is it?

06:53.664 --> 06:54.915
- It's...

06:56.041 --> 06:57.918
It's everything!

06:57.918 --> 07:00.838
- If it's so important, why did you leave
it out in the open? What's it for?

07:00.838 --> 07:03.674
- [quietly]: You've gotta get it back.
You've gotta get it back...

07:03.674 --> 07:05.884
[slurring]:
because everything knows that we're there.

07:05.884 --> 07:08.470
[speaking gibberish]
- Grandma?

07:08.470 --> 07:10.389
♪

07:10.389 --> 07:11.849
[slurring]:
As a spine!

07:11.849 --> 07:15.018
- She's having a stroke...
- Get help. Get help, Callie!

07:15.018 --> 07:17.354
CALLIE: We need a medic!
- It's okay. I'm right here.

07:17.354 --> 07:19.106
- [slurring]: Doctor... Burelli!

07:19.106 --> 07:21.650
- Dr. Burelli! Burelli!
What's she got to do with it, Grandma?

07:22.693 --> 07:23.694
- Grandma?

07:23.694 --> 07:25.070
♪

07:25.070 --> 07:27.948
- 100... 93...

07:27.948 --> 07:31.159
86...
- Shh... Just rest, Dennis.

07:34.288 --> 07:36.248
You've got a big day ahead of you.

07:39.793 --> 07:42.796
♪ theme song ♪

07:53.140 --> 07:55.684
[birds chirping]
[sighs]

08:01.273 --> 08:03.734
- I thought you were
working from home today.

08:03.734 --> 08:06.320
- I was. West Coast is killing me.

08:06.320 --> 08:08.572
- Hm. All those fake conference calls?

08:08.572 --> 08:10.282
[pouring coffee]
- Very funny.

08:10.908 --> 08:12.284
So, the...

08:12.284 --> 08:15.329
Angel-A of Death, huh?

08:15.329 --> 08:16.955
Do we need to talk about me and Angela?

08:16.955 --> 08:19.082
- I'd love to. How'd you meet?

08:19.583 --> 08:22.294
- She was the listing agent for the house.
Not a bad perk, huh?

08:22.294 --> 08:24.463
- Are you serious?
- I was trying to be funny.

08:24.463 --> 08:27.382
- No, I mean are you guys serious?
- You know what? That's a good question.

08:27.382 --> 08:29.301
I haven't quite worked up
the courage to talk about it yet.

08:29.301 --> 08:31.512
So, when does my character get a cover?

08:31.512 --> 08:32.929
- [scoffs] Please, Dad.

08:32.929 --> 08:35.432
"The Brain" isn't exactly cover material.

08:35.432 --> 08:38.143
You know? He's just... a boring blob.

08:38.143 --> 08:40.312
- Ooh. A little too real.

08:41.647 --> 08:44.399
Where did I put my tie clip?

08:44.399 --> 08:47.402
♪

08:50.155 --> 08:51.698
[opens briefcase]

08:59.456 --> 09:01.166
♪

09:03.919 --> 09:05.295
What are you doing?

09:05.295 --> 09:07.047
You can't be snooping
through my work stuff, Belinda.

09:07.047 --> 09:08.715
[shuts briefcase]
It's confidential. You know that.

09:08.715 --> 09:10.759
- I just needed a fine point
to ink the cover.

09:10.759 --> 09:13.220
Your clients' secret identities
are safe from me.

09:13.220 --> 09:14.471
[grabs briefcase]

09:14.471 --> 09:16.682
- Just ask next time.
- Okay.

09:16.682 --> 09:19.393
♪

09:19.393 --> 09:22.980
- Love you.

09:24.648 --> 09:26.650
[footsteps receding]
[door opens]

09:28.068 --> 09:29.111
[door shuts]

09:29.570 --> 09:31.780
- Is Grandma gonna be okay?
FRANK [on phone]: Um,

09:31.780 --> 09:33.657
I don't know. It's too soon to tell.

09:33.657 --> 09:36.285
Prison doctor said he would keep us
updated on her condition.

09:36.285 --> 09:38.996
- Should Aunt Trudy and I come up?
FRANK: No, no.

09:38.996 --> 09:40.998
They're not accepting
visitors now anyways.

09:42.249 --> 09:44.668
You okay?
- Yeah. Are you?

09:44.668 --> 09:46.378
FRANK [phone]:
Yeah, it was just scary.

09:46.837 --> 09:48.839
She was trying to tell me something, Joe.

09:48.839 --> 09:49.965
♪

09:49.965 --> 09:51.842
All I could make out was "Dr. Burelli."

09:51.842 --> 09:54.052
- Wait, Dennis' psychiatrist?

09:54.052 --> 09:55.596
What's the connection?

09:55.596 --> 09:57.639
- I don't know,
but she could be dangerous.

09:57.639 --> 09:59.725
Me and Callie are on our way
back to Bridgeport now.

09:59.725 --> 10:01.059
You need to keep an eye on Dennis.

10:01.059 --> 10:03.353
- Okay, I'm on it.
[hangs up]

10:06.565 --> 10:09.610
♪

10:12.613 --> 10:14.615
- I got some sustenance for the road.

10:14.615 --> 10:18.118
Red licorice for me, black licorice
for you 'cause you're gross.

10:18.118 --> 10:19.786
- We need to follow him.

10:20.996 --> 10:22.789
CALLIE:
Who?

10:22.789 --> 10:24.249
FRANK:
George. George is in the car.

10:24.249 --> 10:26.168
- Frank, there's no car.

10:27.002 --> 10:28.504
Are you having a vision right now?

10:29.838 --> 10:32.007
[engine rumbling]

10:32.007 --> 10:33.634
- He's leaving. Come on.

10:33.634 --> 10:35.802
Let's go.
- What about Dr. Burelli?

10:35.802 --> 10:37.930
- This is important. Trust me.

10:37.930 --> 10:39.389
I'll tell you where to go.

10:40.516 --> 10:42.518
♪

10:48.607 --> 10:50.317
- Listen, I'm an idiot, okay?

10:50.317 --> 10:52.319
I never should have said
your dad was shady.

10:52.319 --> 10:55.781
He's not shady. He's obviously
getting played by Angela.

10:56.532 --> 10:58.075
Angela's the problem,

10:58.075 --> 11:00.077
so let's forget about
your dad for a moment

11:00.077 --> 11:02.329
and focus on her and her lying

11:02.329 --> 11:04.164
because we need to expose her.

11:04.164 --> 11:06.166
♪ radio playing ♪

11:06.166 --> 11:08.335
- Okay.
- Okay?

11:08.335 --> 11:09.837
- Okay.
- Okay.

11:09.837 --> 11:11.713
So, I was thinking

11:11.713 --> 11:14.049
I'll get my dad to take us all
out to dinner tonight.

11:14.049 --> 11:16.677
Somewhere public.
We ask her some hard questions,

11:16.677 --> 11:18.428
back her into a corner
that she can't get out of.

11:18.428 --> 11:19.721
[door bell ringing]

11:19.721 --> 11:22.349
- Speaking of the devil.
Think we might've summoned her.

11:22.349 --> 11:23.809
- She's coming over. Be cool.

11:23.809 --> 11:25.435
- I'm always cool.
- Shh.

11:25.435 --> 11:27.229
- Hey, you two.

11:27.229 --> 11:28.981
- Hey...
- I thought that was

11:28.981 --> 11:31.525
your very yellow truck
parked out there, Chet.

11:31.525 --> 11:34.444
You know, I swear I saw it
the other day, too.

11:34.903 --> 11:37.406
Parked down the block
from the Estabrook estate.

11:37.406 --> 11:38.782
What were you doing there?

11:38.782 --> 11:40.325
- What were you doing?

11:40.325 --> 11:42.452
- Working on a proposal for Gloria.

11:42.452 --> 11:44.329
- No way. She'd never sell the place.

11:44.329 --> 11:46.206
- No, but I have a unique property

11:46.206 --> 11:48.208
I think she would find quite interesting.

11:48.208 --> 11:51.420
In fact, I'd love to tell you
more about it, Chet.

11:52.004 --> 11:54.965
- Me? Why?
- Come by my office tonight.

11:54.965 --> 11:56.884
You know where it is, right?

11:56.884 --> 11:58.302
The Hardy Boys can give you directions.

11:58.302 --> 12:00.679
- We'll be there.
- Great.

12:00.679 --> 12:02.639
♪

12:02.639 --> 12:04.141
I'll see you then.

12:05.017 --> 12:07.853
[door opens, bell rings, door shuts]

12:07.853 --> 12:09.104
- What did you just agree to?

12:10.480 --> 12:11.523
[sighs]

12:11.940 --> 12:13.942
[elevator dings]
PHIL: Hey.

12:14.735 --> 12:16.653
Where's Biff?
- She stopped on the third floor

12:16.653 --> 12:19.364
to see her mom. What's going on?
- Well, we got a problem.

12:19.364 --> 12:21.783
Lucy came to see Dennis,
but they moved him to a different room,

12:21.783 --> 12:23.911
and now the door's locked,
and no one's allowed in.

12:23.911 --> 12:25.412
- Wait, Lucy's here?

12:25.954 --> 12:28.832
[indistinct PA announcement]

12:30.375 --> 12:31.919
[sighs, sniffles]

12:31.919 --> 12:34.296
Hey there. Is everything alright?

12:35.172 --> 12:36.590
- Th-they're moving Dennis

12:36.590 --> 12:39.301
to the Dixon Institute for...

12:39.301 --> 12:41.011
neuro... something.

12:41.011 --> 12:42.513
♪

12:42.513 --> 12:44.515
They won't even let me
see him to say goodbye.

12:45.849 --> 12:47.851
- Maybe that's a good thing?

12:47.851 --> 12:50.395
I-- The-the first part,
not the second part.

12:51.355 --> 12:53.857
[elevator dings]
Maybe it'll help him get better.

12:54.900 --> 12:58.570
- I just don't understand why
Dr. Burelli's moving him now.

12:58.570 --> 12:59.613
What changed?

12:59.613 --> 13:01.657
- Wait. Dr. Burelli's moving him?

13:01.657 --> 13:04.076
When?
- Tonight.

13:04.076 --> 13:05.536
- His parents are okay with this?

13:05.536 --> 13:07.538
- She told them it was for the best.

13:07.538 --> 13:10.832
[footsteps]

13:14.753 --> 13:15.754
[beep]

13:16.588 --> 13:17.923
- I bet she did.

13:17.923 --> 13:19.466
[door shuts]
- What does that mean?

13:19.466 --> 13:21.176
- Okay. Lucy, you trust me, right?

13:23.345 --> 13:26.348
♪

13:26.348 --> 13:28.934
[indistinct PA announcement]

13:28.934 --> 13:32.229
[hospital chatter]

13:44.825 --> 13:46.326
- Did you want me to fax
that for you, Doctor?

13:46.326 --> 13:48.704
- Uh, n-no. That's alright.
I just need to double-check the number

13:48.704 --> 13:50.998
for the Dixon Institute
for Neurophysiology.

13:50.998 --> 13:52.332
NURSE:
Okay. Mm-hmm...

13:52.332 --> 13:53.834
Yep. That's right.

13:55.377 --> 13:58.422
[banging]
- Ah! Pudding pies!

13:58.422 --> 14:01.592
- Give me back my money! Come on!

14:01.592 --> 14:03.010
[nervous laugh]

14:03.010 --> 14:04.511
I love chips.

14:04.511 --> 14:05.888
♪

14:05.888 --> 14:08.849
[rattling]
Ah, it's coming!

14:08.849 --> 14:11.435
It's almost there!
It's getting really, really close!

14:11.435 --> 14:12.686
[shaking machine]

14:14.479 --> 14:15.522
[door shuts]

14:20.277 --> 14:22.696
[dial tone]
[sighs]

14:22.696 --> 14:24.698
[dialing]

14:27.993 --> 14:30.871
DR. BURELLI: I did what you asked.
You'll have the boy at 8:00.

14:30.871 --> 14:35.000
But, you need to know--
[click, dial tone]

14:35.000 --> 14:37.002
[sighs]
[hangs up]

14:44.510 --> 14:47.346
[door opens, shuts]

14:52.601 --> 14:54.228
[sighs]

14:54.228 --> 14:56.313
- That was way too close.
- I've had closer.

14:58.023 --> 14:59.024
[thud]

15:02.945 --> 15:05.447
It's Dennis' transfer form.

15:05.447 --> 15:07.324
Something tells me they're
not moving him to Dixon City.

15:07.324 --> 15:08.367
- We have to go.

15:09.701 --> 15:11.119
- I'll be right behind you.

15:14.748 --> 15:17.543
[picks up phone, pushes button]
[dial tone]

15:17.543 --> 15:20.295
[redialing]

15:20.295 --> 15:23.841
[insects chirping]

15:23.841 --> 15:25.467
[altered voice]:
What is it now, Doctor?

15:25.467 --> 15:28.428
♪

15:28.428 --> 15:30.931
[heavy breathing]

15:30.931 --> 15:33.183
[breathing on phone]

15:34.893 --> 15:37.646
[dial tone]

15:37.646 --> 15:38.647
[hangs up]

15:42.651 --> 15:44.027
♪

15:46.029 --> 15:47.739
- What are you doing in my office?

15:47.739 --> 15:50.909
- I was...
[hallway chatter]

15:50.909 --> 15:52.578
I was actually looking for you.

15:53.161 --> 15:55.706
I have a few questions
about my friend Dennis.

15:55.706 --> 15:57.875
Why can't we see him?
Why are you moving him now?

15:57.875 --> 15:59.293
- To fully recover.

15:59.293 --> 16:02.254
He needs a facility that
specializes in neurophysiology.

16:03.213 --> 16:04.548
- Well, then why did you throw this out?

16:04.548 --> 16:06.675
- Because it's already been faxed.

16:06.675 --> 16:08.552
- You don't keep records of
your patients' transfer orders?

16:08.552 --> 16:11.305
- I also don't explain myself to kids.

16:11.305 --> 16:13.265
- Why didn't
the Dixon City Institute pick up

16:13.265 --> 16:15.142
when I hit redial on your phone just now?

16:15.142 --> 16:16.185
♪

16:16.185 --> 16:18.520
- You really did something
you shouldn't have.

16:20.105 --> 16:21.231
- Why'd you come to Bridgeport?

16:21.231 --> 16:23.567
How do you know Gloria Estabrook?
- Security.

16:23.567 --> 16:26.320
I caught this boy snooping in my office
and messing with my files.

16:26.320 --> 16:29.698
I want him escorted from the building
immediately and banned from returning.

16:29.698 --> 16:32.034
Unless, of course, he finds
himself terribly injured.

16:32.034 --> 16:33.452
SECURITY:
Let's go, kid.

16:33.452 --> 16:35.662
JOE:
Alright, take it easy. I'm going.

16:35.662 --> 16:37.164
♪

16:39.333 --> 16:40.584
Let's go.
LUCY: Where?

16:40.584 --> 16:42.169
- My house. I'm banned from the hospital.

16:42.169 --> 16:44.087
Burelli knows The Shadow Man.
She's gonna give him Dennis.

16:44.087 --> 16:45.589
- But what do they need Dennis for?

16:45.589 --> 16:47.174
- What's a Shadow Man?
- I'll explain on the way,

16:47.174 --> 16:49.510
but we need to stop Burelli
from moving Dennis before it's too late.

16:49.510 --> 16:51.929
- Stop her how?
- We're gonna move him first.

16:54.556 --> 16:57.726
BIFF: You want to heist Dennis?
- This is crazy risky. I love it.

16:57.726 --> 16:59.978
- We're not going to heist him.
We're going to hide him.

16:59.978 --> 17:02.523
Dennis'll be safe in the hospital,
just not in his room.

17:02.523 --> 17:05.108
- Are you sure the transfer is fake?
- Uh yeah, pretty sure.

17:05.108 --> 17:06.609
When I redialed the number
on Burelli's phone,

17:06.609 --> 17:08.819
all I got was a modulated voice.
- Like an operator?

17:08.819 --> 17:12.491
- Like a killer, Phil! Like the guy that
Lola said hired her to do the bombing.

17:12.491 --> 17:14.992
So, unless the Dixon City Neuro-whatever

17:14.992 --> 17:16.744
is run by a heavy-breathing creeper,

17:16.744 --> 17:18.204
Dennis is in big trouble.

17:18.872 --> 17:20.874
That's where we come in.

17:22.291 --> 17:24.795
[lamp smash]
Careful. Someone broke a lamp.

17:24.795 --> 17:27.881
LUCY: Shouldn't we tell
Dennis' parents or the police?

17:27.881 --> 17:29.174
- And say what?

17:29.174 --> 17:32.094
Look, Burelli has power, authority,
and respect on her side.

17:32.094 --> 17:35.055
Okay? Unless we have proof,
it's our word against hers.

17:35.055 --> 17:37.641
The only way this op works
is if you guys are on the inside,

17:37.641 --> 17:39.017
and I'm running it from the outside.

17:39.017 --> 17:41.270
♪

17:41.270 --> 17:42.896
Where are my walkie-talkies?

17:42.896 --> 17:44.356
- Oh, the walkies are in
my locker at school!

17:44.356 --> 17:46.817
- Why didn't you say anything?
- Why didn't you say anything?

17:46.817 --> 17:47.901
- [sighs] Okay.

17:47.901 --> 17:50.320
Lucy, you need to get us
a floor plan of the hospital.

17:50.320 --> 17:52.030
You two get the walkies and meet me

17:52.030 --> 17:54.741
in the hospital parking garage
at the van. Got it?

17:54.741 --> 17:56.285
PHIL/BIFF/LUCY:
Got it.

17:56.285 --> 17:57.494
- What van?

18:03.917 --> 18:05.586
- Hey!
- Ah!

18:05.586 --> 18:07.171
What are you doing?

18:07.171 --> 18:08.839
- Sorry! Didn't mean to scare you.

18:09.840 --> 18:11.466
- My nerves are shot.

18:12.342 --> 18:14.761
- Thought you might want some company

18:14.761 --> 18:16.388
and your sweater.

18:17.806 --> 18:19.057
- Thank you.

18:19.641 --> 18:20.976
You want a fry?

18:20.976 --> 18:22.269
- Sure.

18:25.981 --> 18:27.482
You know...

18:27.482 --> 18:28.984
Jesse's lucky to have you.

18:29.985 --> 18:31.653
I mean, we all are.

18:32.404 --> 18:33.989
Dad, Frank, me.

18:35.032 --> 18:36.283
Biff.

18:37.201 --> 18:39.244
It's just you take care of everyone.

18:40.996 --> 18:42.581
Don't know what we'd do without you.

18:44.249 --> 18:46.251
- Oh, you want something, don't you?

18:47.044 --> 18:48.837
- I mean, I'll take another fry.

18:49.713 --> 18:50.839
- All yours.

18:53.050 --> 18:55.511
[sighs] I better get back in there.

18:56.720 --> 18:59.806
I'm, uh, reading to Jesse.

19:01.058 --> 19:04.520
Hoping if I butcher enough Russian names,
she'll wake up and correct me.

19:04.520 --> 19:05.771
- Solid plan.

19:05.771 --> 19:06.980
♪

19:06.980 --> 19:09.483
You know, why don't
I clean up in here for you?

19:10.442 --> 19:12.027
Least I can do.

19:12.653 --> 19:15.155
- You... want to clean up my van.

19:15.906 --> 19:18.742
- Well, I mean, it kinda smells
like my gym bag in here, so...

19:18.742 --> 19:19.743
[laughs]

19:20.827 --> 19:22.329
- Okay. Um, just...

19:22.996 --> 19:25.040
lock up when you're done.

19:26.959 --> 19:27.960
[door creaks, shuts]

19:28.627 --> 19:29.628
[sighs]

19:30.212 --> 19:31.672
Joe?

19:32.965 --> 19:34.675
Thanks for checking in on me.

19:35.300 --> 19:36.885
You got it.
[taps door]

19:38.345 --> 19:40.347
[walks away]
[Joe sighs]

19:41.098 --> 19:44.101
♪

19:52.943 --> 19:54.236
- Are those phone books?

19:54.236 --> 19:56.280
Why do you have those phone books? Phil?

19:56.280 --> 19:58.448
What did you do?
- I didn't do anything, I swear.

19:58.448 --> 20:01.326
Look, you said your birth mom wasn't
listed in the Bridgeport phone book,

20:01.326 --> 20:03.579
so I checked the surrounding
areas for their phone books.

20:03.579 --> 20:05.581
Th-that's all I did, and...

20:05.581 --> 20:07.332
this was before your mom got hurt and...

20:07.332 --> 20:09.418
[sighs] Please don't be mad.

20:09.418 --> 20:10.669
♪

20:11.295 --> 20:14.298
- I'm not mad, but I'm not looking
for Abigail Owens anymore.

20:15.716 --> 20:18.510
My mom is my mom, and when she wakes up,

20:18.510 --> 20:19.928
everything will go back to normal.

20:19.928 --> 20:22.264
- Totally. And I should probably
get rid of these, I mean...

20:22.264 --> 20:24.641
- Hey, you two. The school's
closed to students today.

20:24.641 --> 20:26.727
- Oh yeah, I know. I was--
I was just getting some stuff.

20:26.727 --> 20:28.812
- Let's go. The janitor's locking up.

20:28.812 --> 20:31.273
- Really sorry to hear
about your mom, Biff.

20:35.110 --> 20:36.320
- [whispers]:
Let's get out of here.

20:36.320 --> 20:38.322
♪

20:43.535 --> 20:45.454
- Come on, he went this way. Hurry.

20:45.454 --> 20:47.539
- If you say so. This is bonkers.

20:47.539 --> 20:49.666
I can't believe I'm following you
following a ghost.

20:49.666 --> 20:50.834
- He's not a ghost.

20:51.376 --> 20:52.503
He's a projection of The Eye.

20:52.503 --> 20:54.338
- [scoffs] Thanks for clearing that up.

20:54.338 --> 20:55.339
[soft chuckle]

20:56.423 --> 20:58.008
- He must've gone in the secret room.
[sighs]

21:00.511 --> 21:02.638
[projector clicks, whirring]
[distorted noises]

21:04.056 --> 21:05.307
CALLIE:
What is it?

21:10.437 --> 21:12.564
FRANK:
Dr. Burelli wrote a book.

21:12.564 --> 21:14.525
This must be what George
is trying to show me.

21:15.025 --> 21:16.568
- Or maybe what Gloria
was trying to tell you.

21:17.653 --> 21:20.781
- Gloria didn't say anything about a book.
- No, but she did say spine.

21:25.536 --> 21:26.828
Bingo.

21:31.625 --> 21:32.876
- It's a secret code.

21:32.876 --> 21:34.127
♪

21:38.507 --> 21:40.133
CHET:
Whoa.

21:40.801 --> 21:43.136
♪

21:50.394 --> 21:51.687
- Dad?

21:51.687 --> 21:53.814
- What are you doing here?
- What are you doing here?

21:53.814 --> 21:55.190
How do you even know about this place?

21:55.190 --> 21:57.150
- I told you, my work is confidential.

21:57.150 --> 21:58.151
ANGELA: Oops.

21:58.986 --> 22:01.655
Did I double book a meeting down here?

22:01.655 --> 22:02.906
Sorry about that.

22:04.449 --> 22:05.450
[sighs]

22:05.951 --> 22:07.578
- You two were never dating, were you?

22:07.578 --> 22:09.204
ANGELA:
No, Belinda.

22:09.204 --> 22:11.331
It would be very inappropriate

22:11.331 --> 22:13.166
for me to date my boss.

22:15.627 --> 22:18.547
- I'm a senior operative
with the Department of Special Affairs.

22:18.547 --> 22:20.757
I manage a team of--
- Kidnappers?

22:21.383 --> 22:24.761
- I didn't know Angela and Mack
took the Hardy Boys until after.

22:24.761 --> 22:26.680
- Need to know, boss.

22:26.680 --> 22:28.891
- You said you take conference calls

22:28.891 --> 22:31.018
and do paperwork.

22:31.018 --> 22:34.021
You lied to me. You've been
lying to me my whole life.

22:34.021 --> 22:36.231
- Belinda... it's me.

22:36.231 --> 22:38.275
Alright? I'm the same guy.

22:38.275 --> 22:40.777
My job is to fix things.

22:41.445 --> 22:44.406
We clean up messes other people make.

22:44.406 --> 22:45.949
That's why we're in Bridgeport.

22:47.034 --> 22:48.410
- It's The Eye, isn't it?

22:48.410 --> 22:51.038
- We're trying to stop the power
from falling into the wrong hands.

22:51.038 --> 22:52.331
- Too late for that.

22:52.331 --> 22:54.208
- What are you talking about?

22:54.208 --> 22:56.376
- I know where the power of The Eye is.

22:56.376 --> 22:58.712
That's actually why I called
this little meeting of the minds.

22:58.712 --> 23:00.422
- Where is it, Angela?

23:00.422 --> 23:02.382
- We tracked it to the Estabrook Estate.

23:02.382 --> 23:05.302
Chet and Belinda already know that.
They were there.

23:06.011 --> 23:07.763
- I see I'm not the only one
keeping secrets.

23:07.763 --> 23:08.972
- Don't even start.

23:08.972 --> 23:11.099
- Frank and Joe were there, too.

23:11.099 --> 23:12.226
One of them used the power

23:12.226 --> 23:14.394
to draw us away
to save one of his buddies.

23:14.394 --> 23:16.855
- How? We have the relic.

23:16.855 --> 23:18.857
- That's right. We have the relic.

23:18.857 --> 23:20.400
♪

23:20.400 --> 23:22.903
Frank Hardy has the power of The Eye.

23:24.071 --> 23:25.739
- Oh, you've gotta be kidding me.

23:25.739 --> 23:28.700
- No, that's... not... Why--
- Don't bother, Chet!

23:29.409 --> 23:31.453
Dumb doesn't suit you.

23:31.453 --> 23:32.788
I saw him on the beach.

23:32.788 --> 23:35.499
- So then why didn't you just
grab Frank on the beach?

23:35.499 --> 23:38.794
- We can't just take it back by force,
can we, boss?

23:41.588 --> 23:43.382
- No.

23:43.382 --> 23:45.300
I've been at Stratemeyer for years.

23:45.300 --> 23:48.679
I've worked closely with people familiar
with The Eye. One thing is clear.

23:49.638 --> 23:52.391
Using the relic, unlocking its power,

23:52.391 --> 23:55.352
requires a willing participant.

23:55.352 --> 23:58.146
If what you're saying is true,
the transfer of power from the relic

23:58.146 --> 24:01.608
to a person would have required
a willing host.

24:02.442 --> 24:03.986
If the power's in Frank?

24:05.112 --> 24:06.905
Frank let it in.

24:06.905 --> 24:09.241
- Now, Frank needs to let it out.

24:09.241 --> 24:11.243
And that's where you come in, Chet.

24:11.243 --> 24:14.162
You're the one who's going to
convince Frank to give it up.

24:14.162 --> 24:19.459
♪

24:19.459 --> 24:21.336
JOE: Okay, guys, it's simple.
We know Burelli eats

24:21.336 --> 24:23.172
in the cafeteria here every night at 7:00.

24:23.172 --> 24:25.382
- Usually.
- What do you mean usually?

24:26.133 --> 24:29.136
- Well, every night I've been there,
she's usually there.

24:30.679 --> 24:32.723
Probably.
- No, we kind of need a definitely.

24:32.723 --> 24:35.142
- Okay, assuming
she sticks to her pattern,

24:35.142 --> 24:37.102
this is where you steal her key card.

24:37.102 --> 24:40.397
It's got the mag stripe on it, which
lets us get into Dennis' room, 407.

24:40.397 --> 24:43.775
Then, we'll take him down
this hall to the north elevators

24:43.775 --> 24:45.819
and into the P5 parking garage here,

24:45.819 --> 24:48.655
and we'll hide him out in this van until
it's safe to bring him back into his room.

24:48.655 --> 24:49.948
- That's a lot of "we" talk
from the guy

24:49.948 --> 24:51.366
that's gonna sit in the van
the whole time.

24:51.366 --> 24:54.077
- What do you want me to do? I'm banned!
It's not like I can sit on your shoulders

24:54.077 --> 24:56.622
under a gown with a surgeon's mask
and pretend to be a doctor.

24:56.622 --> 24:58.081
Unless...

24:58.081 --> 24:59.791
- No!

24:59.791 --> 25:01.585
- No! No, no.
We need to stick to the plan.

25:01.585 --> 25:03.504
Okay, we have to stop Burelli's
hand-off to the Shadow Man.

25:03.504 --> 25:05.255
It's not a perfect play,

25:05.255 --> 25:06.632
but desperate times, desperate measures.

25:06.632 --> 25:08.133
- We really doing this?

25:08.133 --> 25:10.010
♪

25:10.010 --> 25:12.513
- You know Dennis best.
What would he say?

25:14.306 --> 25:16.934
- Dennis loves heist movies.

25:16.934 --> 25:19.436
He'd say, "Thanks for having my back."

25:22.189 --> 25:24.191
[insects chirping]

25:24.191 --> 25:27.194
- It's not a Hill cipher
or Playfair cipher

25:27.194 --> 25:29.488
or a Vigenère.
- We've got to be missing something.

25:29.488 --> 25:31.907
Gloria begged us to find that crystal.

25:31.907 --> 25:33.575
What's the connection to the book?

25:33.575 --> 25:36.620
- Burelli wrote the book.
Maybe she wrote the code, too?

25:37.746 --> 25:38.789
- Right.

25:40.207 --> 25:43.252
And then Gloria put the code
in the spine of this book...

25:43.252 --> 25:45.587
- Because the book is the cipher.

25:45.587 --> 25:47.047
Like an Ottendorf code!

25:47.047 --> 25:50.050
Let's say the first row
of numbers equals the page,

25:50.050 --> 25:53.178
the second row is the line on each page,

25:53.178 --> 25:55.430
and the third row is the word.

25:55.430 --> 25:58.225
So that's page 47,

25:58.225 --> 26:00.477
line 21, word three.

26:00.477 --> 26:01.895
♪

26:01.895 --> 26:02.938
What's that?

26:04.481 --> 26:05.983
- "Project."

26:07.192 --> 26:08.694
There was a projector in my vision.

26:09.862 --> 26:11.363
Keep going, this feels right.

26:12.531 --> 26:15.242
- Okay. Um... Page 81...

26:15.909 --> 26:17.160
[walkie talkie-static]
- Everyone set?

26:17.160 --> 26:18.495
PHIL [on walkie]: Set.
LUCY [on walkie]: Check.

26:18.495 --> 26:20.873
- Good to go. Over.
[click]

26:20.873 --> 26:24.126
♪ We Got The Beat by The Go-Gos ♪

26:27.713 --> 26:30.299
- Oh!
- Oh no! I'm so sorry!

26:30.299 --> 26:31.425
[click]

26:31.425 --> 26:33.927
- Stop. It-it's fine. Thank you.

26:36.221 --> 26:37.222
[sighs]

26:37.222 --> 26:40.184
♪ See the people walking down the street ♪

26:40.184 --> 26:43.103
♪ Fall in line,
just watching all their feet ♪

26:43.645 --> 26:46.148
♪ They don't know where they want to go ♪

26:46.148 --> 26:48.150
♪ But they're walking in time ♪

26:48.775 --> 26:51.528
♪ They got the beat, they got the beat ♪

26:51.528 --> 26:53.655
♪ They got the beat ♪

26:53.655 --> 26:54.948
[walkie-talkie static]

26:54.948 --> 26:57.159
- Phase one complete.
- Copy.

26:57.159 --> 26:59.119
Phase two when clear.
[click]

27:00.120 --> 27:03.498
- Oh! Oh no! Excuse me, I-I believe that

27:03.498 --> 27:04.791
Dr. Burelli lost this.
- Oh.

27:04.791 --> 27:06.668
- I think she dropped it, obviously.

27:06.668 --> 27:07.961
- Yeah.
- Do you think it's important?

27:07.961 --> 27:10.005
I think it's important
because it has her name on it.

27:10.005 --> 27:12.090
Is there a lost and found here, so I...
- No.

27:12.090 --> 27:13.926
No, there isn't.
No, I'll just take it. Thank you.

27:13.926 --> 27:15.260
Thanks.
- I love your sweater.

27:15.260 --> 27:17.679
- Is that wool? Brings out your eyes.
NURSE: It is. Thank you.

27:17.679 --> 27:19.973
- I'll make sure she gets it.
- Okay. Thank you.

27:21.141 --> 27:24.228
♪ All the kids just
getting out of school ♪

27:24.228 --> 27:26.146
[walkie-talkie static]
- Package en route.

27:26.146 --> 27:28.273
♪ Acting cool, hang around... ♪

27:28.273 --> 27:30.484
- Don't worry. I got you.
- Come on!

27:32.694 --> 27:35.030
♪ They got the beat, they got the beat ♪

27:35.030 --> 27:37.783
- Burelli's on the move.
JOE [on walkie]: You guys better hurry.

27:37.783 --> 27:39.701
Coast is clear on P5.

27:40.285 --> 27:41.995
- Dr. Burelli!

27:41.995 --> 27:44.498
Someone turned this in for you.
You must've dropped it.

27:46.458 --> 27:48.001
♪ Go-go music really makes us dance ♪

27:48.001 --> 27:49.044
- Oh no.

27:49.711 --> 27:51.213
We've got a problem.

27:51.213 --> 27:53.257
♪ Puts us in a trance ♪

27:53.257 --> 27:55.217
♪ The Watusi, just give us a chance ♪

27:55.217 --> 27:57.886
- North elevators are a no-go.
We need an alternate route.

27:58.303 --> 28:01.515
- Your only option is the south elevator.
Backtrack and avoid Burelli.

28:02.391 --> 28:03.684
- Copy.

28:03.684 --> 28:05.143
♪ Yeah, we got it ♪

28:05.143 --> 28:06.395
We're improvising.

28:07.187 --> 28:08.897
- Hang in there, Dennis.

28:08.897 --> 28:10.816
♪ Everybody, get on your feet ♪

28:10.816 --> 28:11.859
♪ We got the beat ♪

28:11.859 --> 28:13.819
♪ We know you can dance to the beat ♪

28:13.819 --> 28:14.945
♪ We got the beat ♪

28:14.945 --> 28:17.656
♪ Jump back, get down ♪

28:17.656 --> 28:20.117
♪ Round and round and round ♪

28:20.117 --> 28:22.119
♪ Woo! We got the beat ♪

28:23.161 --> 28:26.164
♪ We got the beat, we got the beat,
we got the beat... ♪

28:26.164 --> 28:29.168
♪ song fades out ♪

28:29.960 --> 28:32.963
[picks up phone]
[dialing]

28:35.340 --> 28:37.176
[beeper beeping]

28:38.468 --> 28:39.678
- Gotta go handle something.

28:39.678 --> 28:42.389
- What? Off to do more
evil things for evil company?

28:43.473 --> 28:45.851
- It's a little more nuanced than that.

28:46.351 --> 28:48.854
Like Prince Valkyrie from your 'zine.

28:50.480 --> 28:51.523
Angela, we're done here.

28:52.232 --> 28:53.859
Kids, go home.

28:56.153 --> 28:59.156
[footsteps receding]

29:00.365 --> 29:01.491
[Belinda sighs]

29:01.491 --> 29:04.411
♪

29:05.537 --> 29:07.539
- Uh, can I borrow your truck?
I need to follow my dad.

29:08.332 --> 29:10.542
- You want me to come with you?
- No. I need to do this alone.

29:10.542 --> 29:13.045
You okay to walk?
- Yeah. Uh...

29:13.045 --> 29:15.172
I gotta do something.
- Okay.

29:16.173 --> 29:17.174
[sighs]

29:20.135 --> 29:23.138
[indistinct PA announcement]

29:23.138 --> 29:25.140
♪

29:29.603 --> 29:31.980
- Oh, Dr. Burelli, I just have
a question here about this patient.

29:32.898 --> 29:33.899
- We're trapped.

29:34.441 --> 29:35.943
[indistinct chatter]

29:35.943 --> 29:38.153
Okay. I got this.

29:39.571 --> 29:40.572
[sighs]

29:42.157 --> 29:44.910
Dr. Burelli! I really wanna see Dennis

29:44.910 --> 29:46.662
before the transfer!
- Lucy, I told you.

29:46.662 --> 29:48.080
He can't have visitors today.

29:48.080 --> 29:50.832
You can arrange to see him
once he's more settled in Dixon City.

29:50.832 --> 29:52.668
- But, it's so far away,

29:52.668 --> 29:54.795
and I can't afford a bus pass,

29:54.795 --> 29:57.256
and my parents won't be able to drive me!

29:57.256 --> 29:59.842
I don't know what to do! [sobbing]

30:00.592 --> 30:02.970
Please! Please!
BURELLI: Okay... Okay...

30:02.970 --> 30:05.305
[sobbing]

30:05.305 --> 30:07.307
♪

30:07.307 --> 30:09.893
- Lucy's out. It's me and Dennis
heading to the south elevators now.

30:09.893 --> 30:12.145
[breaking up]:
We'll radio when we're through. Over.

30:12.145 --> 30:14.064
- Biff?
[crackling]

30:14.064 --> 30:16.441
Biff! I don't copy! What happened?

30:16.441 --> 30:19.027
[crackling]

30:19.027 --> 30:21.947
- Hang in there, Dennis. Almost home.

30:21.947 --> 30:23.490
[elevator dings]

30:23.490 --> 30:26.368
- It's all about the image
you present to the public.

30:26.368 --> 30:28.412
The image I wanna...
Wait a minute.

30:28.412 --> 30:29.621
♪

30:29.621 --> 30:31.331
Is that Elizabeth Hooper?

30:33.000 --> 30:34.626
Get over here, kiddo!

30:34.626 --> 30:36.670
- N-- I-I'm good. That's okay.

30:36.670 --> 30:40.174
- Nonsense. This is perfect timing!
Jeff, we're gonna get

30:40.174 --> 30:43.635
a photo of the two of us standing vigil
in front of Chief Hooper's door, alright?

30:43.635 --> 30:46.013
- I'm burned. Get to P5 ASAP.
[click]

30:47.472 --> 30:51.226
- Let's go. This is going to make
some magic. Let's do this.

30:51.894 --> 30:54.229
[rumbling]

30:54.730 --> 30:57.524
- I'm headed to P5 South to meet Dennis.
I'm almost there.

30:58.192 --> 31:00.903
[static, voice breaking up]
- Phil?

31:01.862 --> 31:03.488
Phil, come in!
[click]

31:07.409 --> 31:09.244
[clicking, elevator dings]

31:09.995 --> 31:12.998
♪

31:12.998 --> 31:14.499
- Oh... shi--

31:16.502 --> 31:18.128
[footsteps]

31:18.128 --> 31:19.922
[heavy breathing]

31:19.922 --> 31:22.299
- I knew you'd be back.
- I need to know what you meant.

31:22.299 --> 31:24.092
That I'm going to be the one
to convince Frank

31:24.092 --> 31:25.928
to hand over The Eye. W-why me?

31:25.928 --> 31:28.055
- You know Frank better than I do.

31:28.055 --> 31:29.973
But from what I understand,
he's got a bit of

31:29.973 --> 31:33.477
an alpha male, hero complex
thing going on.

31:33.477 --> 31:36.313
The kind of guy who
steals your girlfriend,

31:36.313 --> 31:38.315
and somehow, you end up saying sorry?

31:39.733 --> 31:41.235
Did I hit a nerve?

31:41.860 --> 31:42.903
Huh.

31:43.320 --> 31:44.905
Maybe I should talk to Callie instead.

31:44.905 --> 31:46.198
- Better stay away from her.

31:46.198 --> 31:48.617
- Does Belinda know you're
holding onto old feelings?

31:48.617 --> 31:50.619
- I'm not h... Don't...

31:51.870 --> 31:55.666
- I want you to understand that if
Frank gives up The Eye willingly,

31:56.333 --> 31:57.793
no one has to suffer.

31:57.793 --> 32:00.796
No one you care about has to get hurt.

32:00.796 --> 32:02.840
Unless that's what you want.

32:02.840 --> 32:05.926
- No! No, that's not what I want!
- Me neither. So...

32:07.344 --> 32:09.096
you're going to help me out?

32:11.139 --> 32:12.558
- Yeah, I'll try.

32:13.016 --> 32:15.894
- Don't try. Just do it.

32:18.981 --> 32:21.984
♪

32:24.278 --> 32:27.656
[sighs]

32:28.198 --> 32:30.450
♪

32:30.450 --> 32:32.327
- You lost Dennis?
- I didn't lose him! I failed

32:32.327 --> 32:34.746
to retrieve him after you lost him!
- Stop!

32:34.746 --> 32:36.290
We need to find him.
He couldn't have gone far.

32:36.290 --> 32:37.958
- Unless someone nabbed him.
- Shut up, Phil.

32:37.958 --> 32:39.585
- Let's split up.

32:39.585 --> 32:41.128
- That way?
- Yeah.

32:42.754 --> 32:44.381
[static]
- Phil, come in!

32:45.674 --> 32:48.427
[static]
Phil? Biff? Lucy? Anyone?

32:49.011 --> 32:50.012
Damn it!

32:51.180 --> 32:52.181
[sighs]

32:54.725 --> 32:57.019
[static]
Come in.

32:58.478 --> 33:00.314
[static]
Come in! Anyone!

33:00.314 --> 33:01.690
[sighs] Come on.

33:03.442 --> 33:04.276
[door opens]

33:04.276 --> 33:07.279
♪

33:10.449 --> 33:11.450
[honk]

33:14.745 --> 33:16.997
[keys jingling]

33:24.254 --> 33:25.756
[Callie sighs]

33:25.756 --> 33:27.132
- How you doing?
CALLIE: Uh, good.

33:27.132 --> 33:28.759
I just have a few more
lines of code to go.

33:28.759 --> 33:30.302
[insects chirping]

33:30.302 --> 33:32.387
I don't think it was
project like projector.

33:32.387 --> 33:34.598
I think it was project like...
[door opens]

33:34.598 --> 33:37.100
[creaking]
like an experiment.

33:37.726 --> 33:40.270
"Project midnight trials underway.

33:40.270 --> 33:44.233
"Vessel A failed to respond.
Transfer aborted.

33:44.233 --> 33:47.236
"Vessel B... prepped for The Sleep Room.

33:48.111 --> 33:50.072
Awaiting your approval."

33:50.072 --> 33:53.075
♪

33:53.909 --> 33:55.410
What is all this?

33:55.410 --> 33:58.288
[high-pitched tone]

34:04.670 --> 34:07.339
[tone continues]

34:11.844 --> 34:14.263
[coughing]

34:16.514 --> 34:19.434
[shuts box, distortion stops]
- There. That's much better.

34:19.810 --> 34:21.103
[panting]

34:21.103 --> 34:23.105
- The crystal's calling me, isn't it?

34:23.105 --> 34:24.606
- Yes.

34:24.606 --> 34:26.400
Would you like to see why?

34:26.400 --> 34:27.818
[whirring]

34:27.818 --> 34:30.987
♪

34:33.156 --> 34:34.574
WOMAN:
Patient B is ready, Nurse Cody.

34:35.659 --> 34:36.909
- What are you doing to my brother?

34:39.496 --> 34:41.623
Joe, snap out of it!
- Get him out of here!

34:42.708 --> 34:44.251
- Frank-- Hey!
It's okay, it's okay, it's okay.

34:44.251 --> 34:45.960
It's me, it's me. You're back.

34:45.960 --> 34:48.088
You're back. What happened?
[panting]

34:48.672 --> 34:50.882
- I think Joe's in trouble.

34:50.882 --> 34:53.342
- Huh?
- Come on.

34:53.342 --> 34:56.346
♪

34:56.346 --> 34:58.265
[keys jingling]

34:59.558 --> 35:00.767
[unlocks door]

35:00.767 --> 35:02.769
- [distorted voice]:
Going somewhere, Doctor?

35:03.770 --> 35:05.772
Where's the kid?

35:06.523 --> 35:08.567
- I don't know.

35:08.567 --> 35:11.069
He's gone.
- We had a deal.

35:11.069 --> 35:13.864
You owe me.
- I'm sorry.

35:14.698 --> 35:16.742
I'm so sorry for what happened,

35:16.742 --> 35:18.452
what we did to you.

35:18.452 --> 35:21.038
But I need you to know that
Midnight won't work on Dennis.

35:21.038 --> 35:24.416
He isn't strong enough.
It won't work on anyone.

35:25.042 --> 35:26.960
- You're lying.
- No.

35:26.960 --> 35:30.214
I tried to tell you. We failed!

35:30.631 --> 35:32.424
There is no vessel strong enough.

35:32.424 --> 35:34.051
PHIL [on walkie]:
Come in, Joe...

35:34.885 --> 35:37.888
♪

35:37.888 --> 35:39.890
[heavy breathing]
[car starts]

35:39.890 --> 35:41.892
[tires squeal]

35:41.892 --> 35:43.393
- No! No!

35:50.442 --> 35:52.486
[car door shuts, engine starts]

35:52.486 --> 35:55.697
[tires squeal]

35:59.660 --> 36:01.370
[grunting, panting]

36:01.370 --> 36:04.289
[tires squeal]

36:04.289 --> 36:06.959
[panting]

36:08.961 --> 36:11.964
♪

36:11.964 --> 36:14.341
[running footsteps]
- 32...

36:14.341 --> 36:17.553
[hallway chatter]

36:17.553 --> 36:20.973
36...
- I found Dennis. He's on the first floor.

36:20.973 --> 36:23.767
PHIL [on walkie]: Oh, thank God.
BIFF [on walkie]: Is he okay?

36:23.767 --> 36:26.979
- Yeah, h-he's in someone's room,
watching TV,

36:26.979 --> 36:29.481
and apparently walking again.
But, he's safe.

36:31.859 --> 36:34.152
Hey. It's me.

36:34.820 --> 36:36.738
- 51...
- It's Lucy.

36:36.738 --> 36:39.032
JOE [on walkie]:
Wait, you guys lost Dennis?

36:42.286 --> 36:45.289
[insects chirping]
[footsteps]

36:45.289 --> 36:48.292
[river burbling]
[engine running]

36:48.292 --> 36:51.295
♪

37:01.930 --> 37:02.931
[sighs]

37:03.348 --> 37:06.393
[rummaging]

37:14.484 --> 37:15.485
[gasps]

37:18.697 --> 37:19.823
[car door slams]

37:20.616 --> 37:21.658
- What are you doing?

37:23.869 --> 37:25.495
- You shouldn't be here.
- In my 'zine,

37:25.495 --> 37:28.040
Prince Valkyrie is a double agent.
Did you know that?

37:28.040 --> 37:31.210
- I knew, and I knew you'd catch on,
but it's not safe here.

37:31.210 --> 37:33.754
- No! Tell me what's going on!
- I will, at home.

37:33.754 --> 37:35.506
- No, Dad, I want the truth now!

37:35.506 --> 37:38.008
- Damn it, Belinda, listen to me!

37:38.008 --> 37:40.511
Angela doesn't know,
so I had to keep up the front.

37:42.095 --> 37:43.305
But I'm a whistle-blower.

37:43.305 --> 37:45.974
♪

37:45.974 --> 37:47.226
Now get out of here.

37:49.520 --> 37:51.522
Go home. I'll meet you there.

37:54.149 --> 37:55.651
[sighs]
[opens door]

37:57.569 --> 37:59.655
[shuts door, shifts gear]

38:00.864 --> 38:03.867
[engine rumbling]

38:07.412 --> 38:08.413
[sighs]

38:16.380 --> 38:18.382
[door opens]
FRANK: Joe?

38:19.258 --> 38:20.509
Joe!
[door shuts]

38:23.345 --> 38:24.930
Hey, man. Hey, where's Joe?

38:24.930 --> 38:27.099
- Uh, he's upstairs with Biff and Phil.

38:27.850 --> 38:29.226
FRANK:
Okay.

38:32.938 --> 38:35.607
Are you good?
CHET: No.

38:35.607 --> 38:37.526
Not really.

38:37.526 --> 38:39.236
I really need to talk to you guys.

38:41.572 --> 38:43.866
- Okay. Um, what's up?

38:44.575 --> 38:45.576
- Um...

38:47.244 --> 38:49.872
I never made a big deal
about you guys getting together,

38:49.872 --> 38:51.498
but the way it happened sucked.

38:51.498 --> 38:53.125
- Chet...
- No, Callie, please.

38:53.125 --> 38:54.751
I need to get this out.

38:56.253 --> 38:59.256
I know I broke up with you,
but it should have been you that did it.

39:00.090 --> 39:02.384
And I think you know that
it shouldn't have been on me

39:02.384 --> 39:04.136
to make it easier for you.

39:05.304 --> 39:08.557
And then you, man, you just
swooped in out of nowhere.

39:09.224 --> 39:12.019
I didn't want to be a jerk,
but what you did wasn't cool.

39:13.145 --> 39:14.438
It hurt.

39:15.772 --> 39:17.232
I know I should've said something earlier.

39:17.232 --> 39:20.485
That's on me, but we all went along
like nothing ever happened.

39:21.195 --> 39:22.863
Then, I felt like I couldn't say anything

39:22.863 --> 39:24.907
because I didn't want
to lose my best friends.

39:26.867 --> 39:28.368
I saw how happy you guys were.

39:29.661 --> 39:31.788
And I tried. Believe me,

39:31.788 --> 39:34.833
I really, really tried
to let go how it all went down,

39:34.833 --> 39:37.544
but... I was mad.

39:38.462 --> 39:39.505
I was mad at you,

39:39.505 --> 39:42.799
but I was really mad at myself
because I never spoke up.

39:45.594 --> 39:46.887
I'm not jealous.

39:47.429 --> 39:48.847
I'm not hung up.

39:50.516 --> 39:52.684
It just all felt unfinished.

39:53.435 --> 39:55.103
- No, you're right.

39:55.103 --> 39:56.939
I made a mistake, and I'm...

39:56.939 --> 39:58.565
I'm glad you said that.

39:59.733 --> 40:02.986
Chet, I'm really, really,
really sorry. Okay?

40:03.946 --> 40:05.656
FRANK:
Hey, me too, man.

40:07.449 --> 40:09.076
I messed up, and I'm sorry.

40:09.701 --> 40:10.702
[sighs]

40:15.249 --> 40:18.877
- Okay. Okay. Appreciate that.

40:22.714 --> 40:23.715
[soft chuckle]

40:24.883 --> 40:26.677
Well, I feel better already.

40:27.761 --> 40:29.513
Oh, there's one more thing.

40:29.513 --> 40:32.140
♪

40:32.140 --> 40:33.725
You're in real trouble, man.

40:34.518 --> 40:37.646
Angela and Stratemeyer Global
are coming for you hard.

40:40.566 --> 40:43.068
- Yeah. Yeah, that sounds about right.

40:45.320 --> 40:46.572
♪

40:47.948 --> 40:50.409
CALLIE:
Okay, so we decoded a secret message

40:50.409 --> 40:51.827
from Dr. Burelli to Gloria.

40:51.827 --> 40:53.453
It was dated almost 10 years ago,

40:53.453 --> 40:55.956
and it mentioned an experiment
called Project Midnight

40:55.956 --> 40:57.916
that happened in a place
called The Sleep Room.

40:57.916 --> 41:00.711
FRANK: There wasn't any information
about what the experiment actually was,

41:00.711 --> 41:03.422
but it required vessels.

41:03.422 --> 41:06.300
We think it might be the crystal.
JOE: No.

41:07.551 --> 41:09.845
- No, it's not the crystal.
The vessels are kids.

41:10.429 --> 41:11.972
I overheard Burelli
talking to the Shadow Man.

41:11.972 --> 41:13.807
He said he wanted to use
Dennis as a vessel.

41:13.807 --> 41:15.434
He must be trying
to restart the experiment.

41:15.434 --> 41:16.518
- What for?

41:17.603 --> 41:19.062
- Revenge.

41:19.062 --> 41:21.356
Burelli was scared. She said she
was sorry for what they did to him.

41:21.356 --> 41:23.233
- There is a kid in my vision.

41:23.233 --> 41:24.860
Burelli had him strapped to a chair.

41:24.860 --> 41:26.820
She was experimenting on him
with some strange machine.

41:28.906 --> 41:31.116
Wait, that's gotta be
the Shadow Man, right?

41:31.116 --> 41:33.285
- Okay, so if we figure out
what Project Midnight was,

41:33.285 --> 41:35.412
we could figure out who Shadow Man is.
BIFF: How?

41:35.412 --> 41:37.122
The kid only exists in visions.

41:37.122 --> 41:39.583
- Now, sure,
but he was a patient back then.

41:39.583 --> 41:41.752
He's either Patient A or Patient B.

41:41.752 --> 41:43.295
He exists somewhere.

41:43.295 --> 41:44.713
FRANK:
You think there might be records?

41:44.713 --> 41:46.131
- It's possible.

41:46.131 --> 41:48.467
We need to figure out exactly
where the experiments took place.

41:48.467 --> 41:50.093
We need to find The Sleep Room.

41:51.845 --> 41:53.222
PHIL:
I mean, what's with that scroll anyways?

41:53.222 --> 41:55.682
Like, the calligraphy's so weird.
What language even is that?

41:55.682 --> 41:56.892
- Shh! I'm trying to think!

41:56.892 --> 42:00.062
- Oh... Okay.
- I could just trigger another vision.

42:00.062 --> 42:01.605
CHET:
Don't. Stratemeyer's tracking you.

42:01.605 --> 42:03.273
FRAN:
So what? They haven't come for me yet.

42:03.273 --> 42:04.816
- Dude, I'm telling you, they will.

42:04.816 --> 42:05.901
- I know where The Sleep Room is!

42:05.901 --> 42:07.653
♪

42:07.653 --> 42:10.072
Frank saw stained glass windows,
a chapel, and a kid

42:10.072 --> 42:11.782
in a navy and burgundy sweat-suit.

42:11.782 --> 42:13.450
Your dad got the scroll
from Dean McFarlane,

42:13.450 --> 42:15.410
the former headmaster at Rosegrave.

42:15.410 --> 42:18.038
Rosegrave has a chapel
with stained glass windows,

42:18.038 --> 42:20.123
and the official colors
are navy and burgundy.

42:20.123 --> 42:22.376
FRANK: Oh my god.
- The Sleep Room's at Rosegrave.

42:22.376 --> 42:23.544
They're experimenting on students!

42:24.920 --> 42:26.588
What? What?
- What?

42:26.588 --> 42:27.589
CALLIE:
What?

42:31.552 --> 42:46.692
♪
